Full Description: Since George started rebuilding engines in 1976, this shop has been his passion. He started the original shop in Covina in 1984. GCH Long Block Racing began rebuilding hot rod engines in the 1970s. Now they are on the cutting edge of Subaru's ever-improving, ever-evolving performance technology. They are a second and third-generation machine shop with a combined total of 65 years of experience. And they are proud to offer top-quality engineering technology. In addition, every job that comes through their shop is custom built to order.   GCH Long Block Racing is entirely in-house, where they have control over what leaves the shop. Each block and head are tested through their rigorous inspection from start to finish by their team of state-certified machinists. They measure their blocks inside and out to ensure the best tolerance levels and specs. They sell rebuilt Subaru engines to Subaru owners, mechanics and other machine shops. Their products are better than others because they do everything in-house with a state-certified master machinist.  GCH Long Block Racing wants to be known for its outstanding craftsmanship, dependability and excellent customer service. The founder's goal was to pass down the shop to his family as it was passed down to him while providing good craftsmanship.

Description: Enhancing MilSim sports with pneumatic-based weapon systems
Headquarters Regions: Greater Los Angeles Area, West Coast, Western US
Full Description: What We Do: AirStrike Systems is a Veteran Owned company which designs and manufactures innovative Paintball and Airsoft weapon systems in the U.S. which enhance gameplay realism and provide players with a competitive advantage. How We Do It: We design our products in-house and rigorously test each product with active MilSim players as they go through product development.  Once a product exceeds our "combat ready" quality assurance tests, they are ready for deployment.  At that point you'll be able to purchase them here. Why We Do It: Damn do we love MilSim sports.  But there is a big disconnect between the military and simulation aspect of our beloved game.  AirStrike Systems was started with the goal of bridging this gap through innovation, community building, and co-creation. Our Mission: To augment MilSim sports through the design, manufacture, and deployment of innovative, realistic weapon systems.  We will enhance gameplay and provide MilSim sports players with a competitive advantage by taking the realism of tactical warfare from the battlefield and placing it in their hands.  Our Vision: To implement AirStrike MilSim products into actual military training IOT provide the most realistic explosive disarmament and deterrence training for U.S. troops available. Our Values: Community:  MilSim sports are, and has always been, a community-centered team sport.  We believe this culture should develop far before the first shot is fired; we believe it starts with sharing, guiding, and co-creation. Honor, Courage, Commitment:  The same principles which apply in the U.S. Marines apply to AirStrike Systems.  As a Veteran Owned business, we take these principles very seriously and believe they are critical in successfully implementing a positive experience for every customer. Giving Back:  When all is said and done, it is how much we are able to give back with which we measure our success.  Therefore, we dedicate ourselves to this philosophy through mentoring, and  fundraising, donating, and volunteering our time at local charity foundations.  If you would like to lend a hand in any of these efforts, head on over to our website (https://airstrikesystems.com/company/) and click on any of the links below to get started with charities we are currently involved with.

The Vantage Spreadsheet eliminated four steps used by many other simulation systems to expand the design hierarchy and translate net-list formats. An IEEE 1076 compiler at the front end of the simulation environment performs a syntax and semantic analysis of a VHDL source file and produces an intermediate data format simulation. Full Description: [PokenZoo.com](http://PokenZoo.com) sells Pokens, the new USB social business card, in the United States. Pokens are small USB devices that allow a user to share personal information like name, address, phone, fax and email with other Poken users. Created by the Swiss company Poken SA, Pokens are extremely popular in Europe and Japan, and began sales in the US in April of 2009. **Poken solves one simple problem:** how do I remember the email addresses and screen names of everyone I meet?  When a user meets other Poken owners in the real world, they quickly swap information. No more writing down email addresses or long blog names. Just touch Pokens and connect. The "digital business card" also shares screen names and profile IDs from a variety of social networking services like MySpace, FaceBook,  Skype, LinkedIn and others. **How a Poken Works** Open an account at http://www.doyoupoken.com and set up your account. Load your social networking profiles, design your "ID Card". Poken users can touch Pokens, and look for the green light as they share Facebook, Twitter and other social network profiles. Users then simply plug the Poken into their computer's USB port, and download the data. **Models and Variety** Pokens come in a variety of shapes and models. As of October 2009, the ones most readily available in the U.S. were the brand new Business Poken "Pulse", the Panda Poken, the Alien Poken, the Ninja Poken, the Geisha Poken, the RapStar Poken, the Caveman Poken, the Rockstar Poken, the VooDoo Poken, the Mad-K Poken, the Poken Ghost, the Poken Bee, the Poken Tigress, the Poken Tiger, the Franky Poken, the Poken Pink Alien, the Poken Fox, the Poken Dragon, the Poken Baby, and the Vampire Poken. The brand new Poken Pulse was introduced in September 2009 in response to requests from corporate customers for a Poken that looked more professional. The Pulse sports a 2GB USB stick in a conservative black style, complete with the integrated Poken sharing technology. **Poken as Marketing and Branding Tool** Corporate customization and marketing integration of the Poken into a company's marketing plan is a specialty of PokenZoo.com. PokenZoo can customize Pokens with logos, specialized printing, and detailed interactive marketing programs. **Affiliate Program** [PokenZoo.com](http://PokenZoo.com) offers the most comprehensive affiliate program available. Approved affiliates earn 20% on sales through ShareASale.com. **Locations** PokenZoo is located in the United States, about 25 miles east of the Minneapolis St. Paul Twin City metro area just across the Minnesota border in Hudson, Wisconsin. **Keep Up With PokenZoo** You can find PokenZoo at the following URLS: [Home Page](http://www.PokenZoo.com)  [PokenZoo Blog](http://www.pokenzoo.com/Poken-Blog)  [FaceBook Page](http://www.facebook.com/pokenzoo)  [Amazon Page](http://www.amazon.com/b?ie=UTF8&me=A280WKHAEV5C66)

Description: Top Gun is a four-month program that combines mentoring with high-impact weekly gatherings.
Headquarters Regions: East Coast, New England, Northeastern US
Full Description: Top Gun is a four-month program that combines mentoring with high-impact weekly gatherings. Top Gun classes will be hosted in Portland, Orono, Brunswick and Lewiston/Auburn. The application process for TopGun 2018 is closed. Please look for 2019 Applications to open in October of 2018. Top Gun identifies high potential entrepreneurs in Maine through a competitive application process in January. In February they are matched with mentors who help guide them as they continue to develop their innovative products, business models, and companies. The classes of six to 12 entrepreneurs in each location will convene weekly for networking, workshopping and mentor meetings over dinner. Sessions can include opportunities for pitch practice, brief presentations by experienced entrepreneurs, and lively discussions about such diverse topics as salesmanship, bootstrapping, hiring, firing and legal issues. The program concludes by bringing together a statewide community of 300 to celebrate and encourage these high potential entrepreneurial teams at the Top Gun Showcase.  Six entrepreneurs are selected through a round of semi-finals in each location to give a five-minute pitch in front of panelists (which may include potential investors, business leaders, and the press). Participants get to engage in the experience of promoting their business to a relevant and appreciative audience.
